    public class MainTabWindow
extends JPanel
    This class represents the majority of the UI. This is a JTabbedPane that organizes the main sections of the program.

    UI Team (Vincent, John, Lina, Gustavo)

              throws Exception

        Throws:

      • makeInternalFrame

        private JInternalFrame makeInternalFrame(String title,
                                         int locationX,
                                         int locationY,
                                         int sizeX,
                                         int sizeY,
                                         boolean boolVisible,
                                         boolean boolResize,
                                         boolean boolIcon)
        A Method that will make the JInternalFrames (ie- the elements in the Dashboard) The parameters will dictate that frames initial values, who will change as the navigates the app.
        Parameters:
        title - String that contains frame title
        locationX - integer of x coordinate of panel on screen
        locationY - integer of y coordinate of panel on screen
        sizeX - integer of panel width
        sizeY - integer of panel height
        boolVisible - boolean that makes panel visible if true
        boolResize - boolean that resizes panel if true
        boolIcon - Whether or not it can be set to the bottom of the screen
        Returns:
        JInternalFrame iFrame
